A strong earthquake measuring 7.8 magnitude struck Wenchuan county of Sichuan Province, leaving at least 12,000 people died and thousands more injured.
Following the earthquake in China's Sichuan Province, Belgian Foreign Minister Karel De Gucht has sent a message of condolence to his Chinese counterpart Yang Jiechi expressing his sympathy with the victims of the disaster.
The State Ethnic Affairs Commission decided to grant 2 million yuan to its provincial branch in the southwestern Sichuan Province for disaster-relief work.
